cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use SPECTRA, please cite the accompanying paper (submitted to ISWC 2026 Resources Track, under review) as well as this software/data record."
type: dataset
title: "SPECTRA: A Traceability Ontology for the 3GPP RAN Standardization Process"
abstract: >-
  SPECTRA is a reusable OWL 2 ontology for modeling the document types,
  relationships, and lifecycle of the 3GPP Radio Access Network (RAN)
  standardization process. The v1.0.0 release contains the ontology TTL,
  SHACL shapes, PyLODE HTML documentation, the full SpectraCQ v1.0
  dataset of 137 competency questions with verbatim company names
  matching the public 3GPP TDOC_List.xlsx, executable Cypher (one file
  per CQ) and
  per-CQ verdict, 15 representative Cypher and 6 representative SPARQL
  queries, an end-to-end synthetic example, a metadata-only real-world
  mini instantiation, a metadata-only cross-WG process KG covering
  RAN1--RAN5, per-WG body-text knowledge graphs (sentence-level
  rendered text retained with explicit 3GPP source attribution,
  following the academic redistribution practice established by
  TSpec-LLM and the GSMA telecom-kg-rel19 release), the sanitized
  parsing pipeline source,
  reproducibility tests (verify_release.py; 25/25 deterministic checks
  across 9 sections), and a validation manifest mapping every
  quantitative claim in the accompanying paper to its supporting JSON
  evidence file. Raw Neo4j instance dumps and VectorDB embeddings are
  not bundled because they exceed the Zenodo size cap and are
  regenerable from the released body-text KGs and pipeline source.
